If you have any problem when you use this skill, you can contact us with email : support@doit.am

DoHome smart home products can help you control household appliances easily and conveniently.
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light.
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust you home light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show.
After connecting Alexa to your DoHome Smart products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "DoHome" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register one DoHome account in our "DoHome smart" app;
(3). You need to have some DoHome smart devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our "DoHome smart" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "DoHome Smart" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "DoHome" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "DoHome", and you'll be navigated to DoHome login page;
(9). Input your DoHome account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished.
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa,discover my devices.”
“Alexa,turn on the bedroom light.”
“Alexa,turn off the bedroom light.”
“Alexa,set the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa,brighten the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa,dim the bedroom light to 50%.”
"Alexa, set bedroom light to green."
"Alexa, set bedroom light to cool white."

Currently this skill supports products:
smart bulb,
smart socket
